file.name: nytimes.com-timeswire-3.0.0-swagger.yaml
file.content:
openapi: 3.0.0
info:
  description: With the Times Newswire API, you can get links and metadata for Times
    articles and blog posts as soon as they are published on NYTimes.com. The
    Times Newswire API provides an up-to-the-minute stream of published items.
  termsOfService: http://developer.nytimes.com/tou
  title: Times Newswire
  version: 3.0.0
  x-apiClientRegistration:
    url: http://developer.nytimes.com/signup
  x-apisguru-categories:
    - media
    - open_data
  x-logo:
    url: https://static01.nyt.com/images/icons/t_logo_291_black.png
  x-origin:
    - format: swagger
      url: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/NYTimes/public_api_specs/master/timeswire/timeswire_v3.json
      version: "2.0"
  x-providerName: nytimes.com
  x-serviceName: timeswire
externalDocs:
  url: http://developer.nytimes.com/
security:
  - apikey: []
paths:
  /content.json:
    get:
      parameters:
        - description: The complete URL of a specific news item, URL-encoded or
            backslash-escaped
          in: query
          name: url
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
      responses:
        "200":
          description: An array of Articles
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                properties:
                  copyright:
                    type: string
                  num_results:
                    type: integer
                  results:
                    items:
                      $ref: "#/components/schemas/Article"
                    type: array
                  status:
                    type: string
                type: object
  "/content/{source}/{section}.json":
    get:
      parameters:
        - description: >
            Limits the set of items by originating source


            all = items from both The New York Times and The International New York Times

            nyt = New York Times items only

            iht = International New York Times items only
          in: path
          name: source
          required: true
          x-consoleDefault: all
          schema:
            type: string
            enum:
              - all
              - nyt
              - iht
        - description: >
            Limits the set of items by one or more sections

            all | One or more section names, separated by semicolons

             To get all sections, specify all. To get a particular section or sections, use the section names returned by this request:
             http://api.nytimes.com/svc/news/v3/content/section-list.json
          in: path
          name: section
          required: true
          x-consoleDefault: all
          schema:
            type: string
        - description: Limits the number of results, between 1 and 20
          in: query
          name: limit
          required: false
          schema:
            type: integer
            default: 20
        - description: Sets the starting point of the result set
          in: query
          name: offset
          required: false
          schema:
            type: integer
            default: 0
      responses:
        "200":
          description: An array of Articles
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                properties:
                  copyright:
                    type: string
                  num_results:
                    type: integer
                  results:
                    items:
                      $ref: "#/components/schemas/Article"
                    type: array
                  status:
                    type: string
                type: object
  "/content/{source}/{section}/{time-period}.json":
    get:
      parameters:
        - description: >
            Limits the set of items by originating source


            all = items from both The New York Times and The International New York Times

            nyt = New York Times items only

            iht = International New York Times items only
          in: path
          name: source
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
            enum:
              - all
              - nyt
              - iht
        - description: >
            Limits the set of items by one or more sections

            all | One or more section names, separated by semicolons

             To get all sections, specify all. To get a particular section or sections, use the section names returned by this request:
             http://api.nytimes.com/svc/news/v3/content/section-list.json
          in: path
          name: section
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
        - description: Limits the set of items by time published, integer in number of hours
          in: path
          name: time-period
          required: true
          schema:
            type: integer
        - description: Limits the number of results, between 1 and 20
          in: query
          name: limit
          required: false
          schema:
            type: integer
            default: 20
        - description: Sets the starting point of the result set
          in: query
          name: offset
          required: false
          schema:
            type: integer
            default: 0
      responses:
        "200":
          description: An array of Articles
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                properties:
                  copyright:
                    type: string
                  num_results:
                    type: integer
                  results:
                    items:
                      $ref: "#/components/schemas/Article"
                    type: array
                  status:
                    type: string
                type: object
servers:
  - url: http://api.nytimes.com/svc/news/v3
  - url: https://api.nytimes.com/svc/news/v3
components:
  securitySchemes:
    apikey:
      in: query
      name: api-key
      type: apiKey
  schemas:
    Article:
      properties:
        abstract:
          type: string
        blog_name:
          type: string
        byline:
          type: string
        created_date:
          type: string
        des_facet:
          items:
            type: string
          type: array
        geo_facet:
          items:
            type: string
          type: array
        headline:
          type: string
        item_type:
          type: string
        kicker:
          type: string
        material_type_facet:
          type: string
        multimedia:
          items:
            properties:
              caption:
                type: string
              copyright:
                type: string
              format:
                type: string
              height:
                type: integer
              subtype:
                type: string
              type:
                type: string
              url:
                type: string
              width:
                type: integer
            type: object
          type: array
        org_facet:
          type: string
        per_facet:
          items:
            type: string
          type: array
        published_date:
          type: string
        related_urls:
          items:
            properties:
              suggested_link_text:
                type: string
              url:
                type: string
            type: object
          type: array
        section:
          type: string
        short_url:
          type: string
        source:
          type: string
        subsection:
          type: string
        thumbnail_standard:
          type: string
        title:
          type: string
        updated_date:
          type: string
        url:
          type: string
      type: object
